description: While presentation makes this pan-fried prosciutto-wrapped salmon feel fancy, the recipe is easy and affordable enough to have on weekly rotation.
name: ProsciuttoWrapped Salmon With Quinoa Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 150g green beans, thinly sliced on an angle

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200Â°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper.
Place tomatoes and capers onto tray. Drizzle with 2 tsp oil and season. Bake for 20 minutes or until softened.

Meanwhile, bring 3 cups water to the boil in a saucepan over high heat. Add quinoa, stir well, reduce heat to medium and simmer for 8 minutes or until cooked. Add beans and cook for 1 minute. Drain and transfer to a large bowl. Cool. Add tomatoes, capers and basil, tossing to combine.

Wrap each salmon fillet with a slice of prosciutto. Heat remaining oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Add salmon and cook for 3 minutes on each side for medium rare or until cooked to your liking. Serve salmon with quinoa salad.
